I spent my 21st birthday doing one of the things that makes me the happiest. Every rodeo I get to tag along too, I’m grateful, grateful that I have the capability to go see new places, spend time on the road with my best friend, meet so many AWESOME new people, and most importantly, get to give @franks_cole19 a big hug after every rodeo. This last year has been a huge struggle of really high highs, and really low lows. And it’s been hard, but I am so thankful for the life we get to live and the huge blessings that we have bestowed. Even though I spent 16 hours of my birthday driving, there isn’t a place I’d rather be (other than maybe on the back of a horse lol) 😉 , @franks_cole19 YOU had a great week and regardless of how the next three weeks go, I’ll always be in your corner ❤️ THANK YOU to everyone who texted, called, or wrote something sweet. I appreciate you. <3 here’s to 21!!!!!! (Also thank you to @rocker_steiner and his family for letting me tag along and being so awesome to franklin)

If there’s anything a 4 year old will teach you, it’s patience. Work hard and trust the process. And I want to thank every single person who has helped or coached me in the last year, and also being patient with me. I appreciate you and y’all know who you are. Also thanking my sweet boyfriend @franks_cole19 for owning him, trusting me, and believing in both of us. Excited to go clean it up a little bit tomorrow <3
